-- Israel Reports Anthrax Kills Eight Cattle on Farm in Hazafon
-- B y   W h i t n e y   M c F e r r o n
-- 2012-08-20T16:43:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-20/israel-reports-anthrax-kills-eight-cattle-on-farm-in-hazafon.html
Israel  reported anthrax killed eight
cattle on a farm in Hazafon, in the northern part of the
country, according to a notification to the World Organization
for  Animal Health , or OIE.  The  outbreak  of the bacterial disease is the first in the
country since 2009, and measures taken include movement controls
and treatment of affected animals with penicillin, according to
the notice published online by the Paris-based OIE. An estimated
174 cattle may be susceptible to the disease, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Whitney McFerron in London at 
